Database management commands.

Examples:
  weg db migrate                    # Run migrations
  weg db console                    # Open database shell
  weg db backup                     # Backup database
  weg db restore backup.sql.gz      # Restore from backup
  weg db trim --days 30             # Trim log tables

Usage:
  weg db [command]

Available Commands:
  console     Open database shell
  migrate     Run database migrations
  query       Run SQL query against database
  trim        Trim log tables to reduce database size

Flags:
  -h, --help   help for db

Global Flags:
  -C, --chdir string              Run as if weg was started in <path>
      --config string             Path to config file (default: auto-detect)
      --debug-categories string   Filter debug output: all,config,state,net,git,fs,exec
      --log-level string          Set log level: quiet, normal, verbose, debug, trace
  -o, --output string             Output format: auto, json, table, plain, quiet (default "auto")
  -q, --quiet                     Suppress non-essential output
  -v, --verbose count             Increase verbosity (-v, -vv, -vvv)
  -y, --yes                       Assume yes for all prompts

Use "weg db [command] --help" for more information about a command.
